    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A humming noise from your ac unit, without the fan spinning, could be a sign that the unit is trying to work but something is blocking the fan or preventing it from turning. First, check if there's any debris or obstruction around the fan blades or the motor. Sometimes, a small piece of debris can cause the fan to hum without spinning. If you find nothing, the issue might be with the fan motor or the motor's connection to the power supply. In that case, you might need to consult a professional. Remember, even the smallest of obstacles can cause a big problem for your ac unit, just like a tiny pebble can cause a big mess in a garden. Keep an eye out for those pesky little things!",
